\section*{Solutions to Problems 6-31 through 6-35}

\subsection*{Problem 6-31}
\textbf{Statement:}\\
What boundary conditions must the scalar magnetic potential \(V_m\) satisfy at an interface between two different magnetic media?

\textbf{Solution:}\\
In current‐free regions one writes \(\mathbf{H}=-\nabla V_m\).  The matching conditions at the interface are:
\begin{align}
&V_{m1}=V_{m2}\quad\text{(continuity of the potential),}\\
&\mu_1\,\frac{\partial V_{m1}}{\partial n}
=\mu_2\,\frac{\partial V_{m2}}{\partial n}
\quad\text{(continuity of the normal component of }B=\mu H\text{).}
\end{align}

